The paper focuses on a specific problem in software engineering, namely code clone detection, which suggests cs.SE as the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of filtering heuristics and an optimized inverted-index, which are techniques commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the scalability and execution time of the proposed method, which suggests the possibility of it falling under cs.IR (information retrieval) or cs.CR (computational complexity).
